cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.SY, cs.RO 

Reasoning: 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is the most likely category as the paper presents a planning domain description language for modelling complex time-dependent effects, which is a common topic in AI research. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is also likely as the paper describes the syntax and modelling style of PDDL+, which is a logic-based language for planning. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is another possible category as the paper introduces a new planning domain description language. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper maps planning instances into constructs of hybrid automata, which are commonly used in control systems. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also possible as planning is a key component of robotics research.
